00:39.637 --> 00:42.355
[ birds chirping ]

00:42.423 --> 00:43.657
[ gasps ]

00:55.786 --> 00:56.819
[ groans ]

01:06.130 --> 01:08.799
[ panting ]

01:25.733 --> 01:27.033
[ gasps ]

02:51.369 --> 02:53.686
[ waterfall rushing ]

03:22.783 --> 03:24.634
[ panting ]

03:41.853 --> 03:44.570
[ stereo playing rock-'n'-roll ]

03:47.658 --> 03:50.626
Excuse me.
Have you seen this woman?

03:50.694 --> 03:51.545
No.

03:51.612 --> 03:53.713
Have you seen this woman?

03:53.915 --> 03:56.332
How 'bout this man here?

03:56.534 --> 03:58.151
Hey, if I were you,

03:58.536 --> 03:59.886
I'd take
those photographs,

03:59.954 --> 04:01.821
and I'd leave.

04:01.889 --> 04:04.157
All right.

04:04.224 --> 04:06.926
[ music playing in Spanish ]

04:26.480 --> 04:29.049
[ woman gasping ]

04:31.051 --> 04:32.819
Wait! Wait!

04:40.060 --> 04:41.361
Wait, wait!
[ gasps ]

04:41.429 --> 04:44.163
Please wait.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

04:44.231 --> 04:46.917
No, stop! Stop! No!

04:48.568 --> 04:49.836
[ yells ]
MAN: No, no, no! Todd!

04:49.904 --> 04:51.237
Todd! Todd! Todd!
She's good.

04:51.305 --> 04:52.555
She's good.
Shit, we gotta go.

04:52.623 --> 04:54.524
Come on! Come on.
Come on! Move!

05:00.547 --> 05:02.516
Come on! Come on!

05:08.689 --> 05:10.089
Erin!

05:10.157 --> 05:11.240
I think we have--

05:11.308 --> 05:13.176
Erin, stop!
Come on!

05:15.763 --> 05:18.164
Wait! What the hell
is going on here?

05:18.232 --> 05:19.965
Wait. Another one?
Yeah, yeah.

05:20.033 --> 05:22.118
What do you mean another one?
Who are you people?

05:22.185 --> 05:24.354
They're bad. We have to go.
Where am I?

05:24.421 --> 05:25.788
Follow us. Come on!

05:41.138 --> 05:42.105
[ sparks crackle ]

05:49.880 --> 05:51.247
[ screams ]

05:56.653 --> 05:58.488
There you go.
Jeez.

05:58.555 --> 05:59.705
What'd she fall, three feet?

05:59.773 --> 06:01.441
Bitch has been pretzeled.

06:01.575 --> 06:03.626
Think she'll live?

06:03.694 --> 06:04.544
No.

06:09.099 --> 06:10.633
[ shallow breathing ]

06:15.055 --> 06:16.472
[ panting ]

06:18.959 --> 06:20.694
Okay, sweetheart, listen to me.

06:20.761 --> 06:22.279
We'll get you out of here.

06:22.346 --> 06:24.697
It's gonna be on a boat.
It's gonna be very choppy.

06:24.765 --> 06:26.983
I'm not sure if you'll be able
to take the pain.

06:28.802 --> 06:32.038
Give me a blink if you want me
to stop the pain.

06:33.724 --> 06:36.175
Give me a blink, sweetheart.

06:37.444 --> 06:38.811
[ neck cracks ]
All right.

06:38.879 --> 06:42.198
Let's get her out of here
while she's still warm.

06:48.706 --> 06:50.039
[ gasps ]

06:50.107 --> 06:51.124
Shh, shh. Shh.

06:53.644 --> 06:56.495
[ sobbing ]

06:56.563 --> 06:57.897
What the hell was that?

06:57.964 --> 07:01.417
Every few days,
they take someone new.

07:01.485 --> 07:03.052
Where do they take them?

07:03.120 --> 07:05.621
We don't know, but if you want
to survive out here,

07:05.689 --> 07:07.123
you have to talk to Quentin.

07:07.190 --> 07:08.558
And this Quentin,

07:08.625 --> 07:10.393
he knows why we're here?

07:10.460 --> 07:12.178
You can ask him yourself.

07:12.246 --> 07:14.063
Let's go.

07:14.131 --> 07:15.648
Come on.

07:31.365 --> 07:33.466
[ beeping ]

07:44.578 --> 07:45.645
What you got for me?

07:45.712 --> 07:47.097
Got a call
from Nikolai in Kiev.

07:47.231 --> 07:49.065
Nothing bad.
He said he's very pleased,

07:49.216 --> 07:52.251
and he has some other business
he'd like to send our way.

07:52.319 --> 07:53.737
That is excellent news.

07:53.804 --> 07:58.341
Also our friend from the east
is coming tomorrow.

07:58.409 --> 08:00.126
Mao? Okay.

08:00.194 --> 08:02.796
Well, then I guess let's make
sure that there's a room prepared.

08:02.863 --> 08:05.899
Mao's not coming alone.

08:07.118 --> 08:08.518
Okay. Well, then I guess

08:08.585 --> 08:12.222
we'll have to make sure that
there are more rooms prepared.

08:18.629 --> 08:20.196
Hey, Chloe.

08:20.264 --> 08:21.530
Where's Erin?

08:21.598 --> 08:22.949
She's gone.

08:23.017 --> 08:24.300
What?

08:24.367 --> 08:26.703
No, no, no, no! Hey!

08:26.770 --> 08:28.804
Chloe, where's Erin?!

08:28.872 --> 08:30.990
Hi.

08:31.608 --> 08:33.676
I love you.

08:39.466 --> 08:40.131
What the hell happened?

08:40.200 --> 08:41.484
They came out of nowhere,

08:41.552 --> 08:42.618
and we got separated.

08:42.686 --> 08:44.035
You're not supposed to separate!

08:51.112 --> 08:52.345
Interesting.

08:52.412 --> 08:54.413
One gets taken.

08:54.481 --> 08:56.098
Another one shows up.

09:02.473 --> 09:04.374
What's your name?

09:05.493 --> 09:07.159
Billie,

09:07.227 --> 09:08.828
Billie Kope.

09:11.799 --> 09:13.400
I'm Quentin.

09:16.287 --> 09:18.237
You can have that hut there.

09:19.790 --> 09:21.474
It was Erin's.

09:23.010 --> 09:25.311
There are some rules you'll
have to hear

09:25.378 --> 09:27.063
before you settle in.

09:27.131 --> 09:28.131
Mr. Quentin!

09:29.016 --> 09:31.317
Thank you so much
for the hospitality,

09:31.384 --> 09:33.453
but I never said I was staying.

09:34.705 --> 09:35.505
You don't have to.

09:35.573 --> 09:36.956
We don't
hold hostages here.

09:37.024 --> 09:40.026
Who were those people
that came after us?

09:41.245 --> 09:43.696
I've got some ideas.

09:43.964 --> 09:45.148
Join us for dinner.

10:02.283 --> 10:03.382
So, Ms. Kope...

10:04.651 --> 10:05.435
what's your story?

10:05.502 --> 10:07.520
Tell us how you got here.

10:07.587 --> 10:09.389
You first.

10:10.457 --> 10:14.244
Heh. They've all heard my story.

10:14.311 --> 10:18.848
You'll find that a lot of the
circumstances are the same.

10:21.352 --> 10:23.186
Yeah, I won a sweepstakes.

10:23.254 --> 10:24.286
[ chuckles ]

10:25.422 --> 10:27.790
Visit paradise. Heh.

10:32.997 --> 10:35.548
The last thing I remember, I was
at a bar in Guatemala.

10:35.616 --> 10:37.717
I was supposed to meet with this
crazy witch doctor dude.

10:37.785 --> 10:41.170
He was gonna get me these
German expats on how to make ayahuasca.

10:41.238 --> 10:42.605
What's ayahuasca?

10:42.672 --> 10:43.973
That's hippie shit.

10:45.443 --> 10:47.343
You got a closed mind, Todd.

10:47.411 --> 10:48.344
No, it's not.

10:49.413 --> 10:50.947
I never got to try it.

10:51.848 --> 10:53.916
[ sighs ]
I was in a bar

10:53.984 --> 10:56.218
drinking some tequila.

10:56.286 --> 10:59.405
Next thing you know, right here,
paradise.

10:59.473 --> 11:00.840
It was about a week ago.

11:00.907 --> 11:02.808
I been here about five days.

11:02.876 --> 11:05.878
I was doing a presentation
in Caracas,

11:05.945 --> 11:07.714
and my head felt weird.

11:07.781 --> 11:09.565
My stomach was hurting.

11:09.633 --> 11:11.333
I thought I had food poisoning,

11:11.401 --> 11:14.120
went to the doctor,
checked on my vital. It was good,

11:14.188 --> 11:16.806
so I went back to the hotel.
Then I passed out.

11:17.108 --> 11:18.291
Then, boom, I am here.

11:18.358 --> 11:20.843
I felt like someone hit me
over the head

11:20.911 --> 11:22.145
with a baseball bat.

11:22.213 --> 11:24.147
I don't remember anything else.

11:25.783 --> 11:27.150
Your turn, Ms. Kope.

11:29.486 --> 11:31.237
Tell us your story.

11:38.095 --> 11:41.914
Have you seen this man?
Do you know him?

11:43.284 --> 11:44.583
No,

11:44.651 --> 11:46.986
but I know someone who does.

11:50.524 --> 11:52.174
Come on.

12:12.129 --> 12:14.597
Look, I don't have anything.

12:15.633 --> 12:17.650
I have no money, nothing, okay?

12:17.718 --> 12:18.984
[ chuckles ]

12:22.355 --> 12:23.606
Catch!

12:39.856 --> 12:41.124
[ blade scrapes ]

12:48.248 --> 12:49.314
[ laughs ]

12:49.382 --> 12:50.566
[ groans ]

12:59.944 --> 13:01.493
[ bone cracks ]
[ yells ]

13:15.709 --> 13:17.226
[ bone cracks ]

13:28.672 --> 13:30.740
[ gasps ]

13:31.658 --> 13:34.543
I guess just like you guys,

13:34.611 --> 13:36.879
I went out to a bar,

13:36.947 --> 13:38.981
I came home...

13:40.817 --> 13:43.352
and the next thing I remember,

13:43.420 --> 13:45.154
I woke up here.

13:55.015 --> 13:57.249
Why don't we all, uh...

13:58.752 --> 14:02.188
have a moment of silence
for Erin?

14:27.331 --> 14:29.949
Walsh, look alive.
We got incoming.

14:40.060 --> 14:42.461
Jesus Christ, what happened?

14:43.079 --> 14:45.031
Occupational hazard.

14:45.098 --> 14:47.015
You killed her?!

14:47.885 --> 14:49.418
She did it to herself.

14:49.486 --> 14:50.235
Yeah, right.

14:50.303 --> 14:53.222
Cut the bullshit.
What happened?

14:53.290 --> 14:54.840
I don't know. Why?
Is there a problem?

14:54.908 --> 14:57.893
Rich, I need you to go over
the stuff for Mao's visit.

14:57.961 --> 14:59.195
Mao's coming? When?

14:59.262 --> 15:00.997
Tomorrow, so be ready.

15:03.100 --> 15:04.784
Walsh, what do you think?

15:04.851 --> 15:06.185
She's still warm.

15:06.253 --> 15:08.587
Gotta get her on the table
and look inside.

15:08.655 --> 15:11.490
If she's not past
her expiration date, then we're good.

15:11.558 --> 15:13.692
Xander, you were there.
What happened?

15:15.145 --> 15:16.712
It's like the Sarge said.

15:16.779 --> 15:18.647
Cut the bullshit.

15:18.715 --> 15:19.965
What happened?

15:22.836 --> 15:25.605
Look, I was
running after her.

15:25.672 --> 15:27.640
I took the shot.
I missed.

15:27.707 --> 15:30.009
She took off.
She fell,

15:30.076 --> 15:32.345
broke her neck.

15:37.501 --> 15:40.302
All right, get her inside.
Hurry.

15:45.208 --> 15:47.609
[ birds warbling,
insects chirping ]

15:51.981 --> 15:55.317
Hey, Billie.

15:55.385 --> 15:57.119
Billie.

15:57.187 --> 15:58.587
Hey, listen.

15:58.655 --> 16:01.957
I know you're, like, freaked out
and stuff, right?

16:02.025 --> 16:03.125
I got your back, baby.

16:03.193 --> 16:04.293
I'll protect you.

16:04.360 --> 16:06.662
I swear to God
I'm so good at that.

16:06.730 --> 16:09.432
I'm good, thank you.

16:13.536 --> 16:15.705
[ sighs ]

16:20.994 --> 16:22.177
Billie.

16:24.781 --> 16:27.483
You know
what sounds good?

16:27.551 --> 16:30.019
Like, a bike ride...

16:30.086 --> 16:33.622
and a nice cup of coffee.

16:34.575 --> 16:37.860
If you need, like, a shoulder
to lean on,

16:37.928 --> 16:40.062
I'm really good for that, too.

16:42.699 --> 16:43.933
Th-Thank you.

16:44.001 --> 16:47.119
And then cuddling naked.

16:51.624 --> 16:53.458
[ sighs ]

17:00.967 --> 17:03.619
Jean, how long
have you been here?

17:03.687 --> 17:05.003
10 days.

17:05.071 --> 17:06.387
And how'd you get here?

17:06.457 --> 17:08.423
I went to San José,
Costa Rica,

17:08.491 --> 17:10.859
for my wisdom tooth
to be removed.

17:10.926 --> 17:13.444
I was visiting
friends in Cancún,

17:13.579 --> 17:15.396
and they didn't want
to go out one night,

17:15.464 --> 17:16.965
so I went out by myself.

17:17.034 --> 17:18.951
Do you remember
where you were before?

17:21.271 --> 17:22.672
Were you in prison?

17:24.074 --> 17:27.093
Yeah, I was,
was in a Mexican prison.

17:28.295 --> 17:30.345
It was just an ounce.

17:30.413 --> 17:32.548
Pulled me over at a checkpoint.

17:34.017 --> 17:36.302
They, uh,
searched my car.

17:36.303 --> 17:37.386
It wasn't hidden very well,

17:37.454 --> 17:38.620
and the rest is history.

17:38.805 --> 17:40.956
Somebody must have slipped
something in my drink,

17:41.024 --> 17:42.291
'cause I started
seeing spots.

17:42.358 --> 17:46.011
They, uh, took me
to this prison doctor,

17:46.079 --> 17:49.215
and he runs, you know,
test after test on me.

17:49.282 --> 17:51.400
I took a cab back home.

17:51.467 --> 17:54.370
I went back to my cell
to sleep, and...

17:54.438 --> 17:57.256
I went back to my hotel...

17:57.324 --> 18:00.092
And I woke up here.

18:00.160 --> 18:03.111
So you go to sleep in
a Mexican prison

18:03.179 --> 18:05.681
and then wake up here?

18:06.633 --> 18:07.883
Yeah.

18:13.006 --> 18:17.243
Is there anywhere I can get a
full view of this island?

18:17.311 --> 18:19.245
Yeah, it's through this way.

18:22.015 --> 18:24.250
You know,
both Berto and Todd

18:24.318 --> 18:27.686
saw the doctor
before they came here.

18:27.754 --> 18:30.423
Yeah, but, uh, Todd was
from Venezuela,

18:30.490 --> 18:33.826
and, uh,
Berto was in Mexico.

18:33.893 --> 18:38.030
So what? Still could be some
connection here.

18:38.098 --> 18:39.498
Even Jean had
been to a dentist.

18:39.633 --> 18:41.918
Had you been to a doctor
before you came here?

18:41.985 --> 18:43.069
Actually, I did.

18:43.136 --> 18:45.804
I got blood work done
in Guatemala City,

18:45.872 --> 18:47.006
malaria test.

18:47.074 --> 18:48.591
Did you have malaria?

18:48.658 --> 18:50.659
No, I'm actually perfectly healthy.

18:52.195 --> 18:55.497
Okay, so all of you have been
to a doctor

18:55.565 --> 18:59.068
and had some kind of
blood work done.

18:59.136 --> 18:59.818
What about you?

19:01.054 --> 19:02.872
No.

19:03.974 --> 19:06.391
How did you know
Berto was in prison?

19:07.194 --> 19:08.677
Lucky guess.

19:10.530 --> 19:13.098
Can I ask you something?
What?

19:13.400 --> 19:15.284
Have you been in prison?

19:17.955 --> 19:19.755
No...

19:19.823 --> 19:21.490
you can't ask.

19:23.060 --> 19:25.194
[ announcements
playing in Spanish ]

19:31.168 --> 19:32.517
You must understand

19:32.585 --> 19:35.404
that in this part of the world

19:35.472 --> 19:39.041
people go missing from
the penal system all the time.

19:39.109 --> 19:40.643
Some escape.

19:40.710 --> 19:44.046
Others buy their way out.

19:44.114 --> 19:45.314
But for your sister,

19:45.382 --> 19:48.284
I'm afraid it may be
something different.

19:49.186 --> 19:52.187
For instance,
someone like yourself,

19:52.255 --> 19:54.957
young woman, attractive,

19:55.025 --> 19:56.608
someone like that,

19:56.676 --> 19:58.610
sometimes...

19:58.678 --> 19:59.711
get sold.

20:00.864 --> 20:02.064
Sold?

20:02.132 --> 20:04.566
Sold to who?

20:06.302 --> 20:09.338
Wait. I need to know
who buys prisoners.

20:09.640 --> 20:11.456
Lower your voice.

20:12.225 --> 20:14.710
I need to know
who bought my sister.

20:16.763 --> 20:17.896
Please.

20:19.132 --> 20:22.301
Okay. I'll do
what I can to help.

20:24.304 --> 20:25.771
And, please,
for your safety,

20:25.838 --> 20:28.641
don't go around asking about
these people,

20:28.708 --> 20:32.094
or you may find yourself
vanishing, too.

20:49.979 --> 20:51.764
Hey, look. There.

20:51.832 --> 20:53.782
Another island.

20:54.501 --> 20:56.285
We need to get there.

20:56.353 --> 20:58.287
Oh, no, Billie, Billie,
like, that--

20:58.355 --> 21:00.222
that island
is five miles off.

21:00.423 --> 21:02.007
That's five miles of
ocean currents.

21:02.074 --> 21:03.575
You get knocked off course,

21:03.643 --> 21:06.878
you're gonna be 20 miles out
before you know what happened.

21:06.946 --> 21:08.313
So what do you suggest,

21:08.381 --> 21:09.615
staying here
and waiting to die?

21:09.649 --> 21:11.249
I'm just saying,
if it was that easy,

21:11.317 --> 21:13.235
don't you think we would have
already swam there?

21:13.303 --> 21:15.137
How can you say
something can't be done

21:15.205 --> 21:16.188
until you actually try it?

21:16.255 --> 21:18.374
So you gonna swim there?

21:20.226 --> 21:22.060
I didn't say that.

21:22.128 --> 21:23.128
Come on.

21:30.654 --> 21:31.554
Good.

21:31.621 --> 21:34.206
There's plenty of wood
for us here.

21:34.273 --> 21:36.341
So we're building a boat?

21:36.510 --> 21:39.361
No, a raft, just enough
to keep us afloat,

21:39.429 --> 21:41.897
and then we'll paddle the rest
of the way.

21:44.550 --> 21:46.168
[ whispering ]
Don't move too fast.

21:46.236 --> 21:47.903
There's someone there.

21:59.366 --> 22:01.933
Little birdies left the nest.

22:03.386 --> 22:04.370
What do you want?

22:04.437 --> 22:05.754
Same thing you do,

22:05.989 --> 22:07.539
to get the hell off this island.

22:07.607 --> 22:09.124
How long you been here?

22:10.927 --> 22:13.328
44 days.

22:13.396 --> 22:14.779
Two months?

22:14.847 --> 22:17.032
How did you
survive out here alone?

22:17.701 --> 22:19.218
What I'm trained to do.

22:19.286 --> 22:20.936
What's your background?

22:22.288 --> 22:24.122
S.A.S.,

22:24.190 --> 22:25.707
British special forces.

22:25.776 --> 22:28.177
I was on exercise
on Honduras,

22:28.245 --> 22:29.578
support and training.

22:29.762 --> 22:31.713
Done a tour in Afghanistan.

22:31.781 --> 22:34.266
Injured twice in the surge.

22:34.334 --> 22:36.551
Survival specialist.

22:37.237 --> 22:38.787
How did you get here?

22:39.805 --> 22:41.156
No idea.

22:41.223 --> 22:43.075
Last thing I remember,

22:43.076 --> 22:45.995
I was traveling along
in a transport van.

22:46.162 --> 22:49.631
We got hit.
There was this massive blast.

22:49.699 --> 22:53.452
Then I just heard Miskito
or maybe Spanish.

22:53.520 --> 22:55.387
Anyway, fell unconscious.

22:55.455 --> 22:58.340
Woke up here.

22:58.407 --> 23:00.075
Do you know
why we're here?

23:00.142 --> 23:01.210
Mm-mm.

23:02.528 --> 23:05.213
But together
we could find out.

23:05.281 --> 23:06.348
No way.

23:07.150 --> 23:08.400
What if he's one of them,

23:08.468 --> 23:09.401
you know, waiting for us

23:09.469 --> 23:11.337
to lead him back to our camp?

23:11.404 --> 23:13.555
Oh, shush, pretty boy.

23:13.623 --> 23:15.807
I know
where your camp is.

23:15.875 --> 23:17.559
I've been there nights.

23:17.627 --> 23:20.696
I could have
strangled every single one of yez,

23:20.764 --> 23:22.781
but I didn't.

23:22.848 --> 23:25.451
The only person
I wanna kill is them.

23:25.518 --> 23:27.719
You have
my word on that.

23:30.690 --> 23:33.709
There's another island
a few miles away,

23:33.777 --> 23:35.694
and I'm gonna try
and get there,

23:35.762 --> 23:38.413
and any of you who want to get
the hell off this island

23:38.481 --> 23:40.615
can come with me.

23:40.683 --> 23:43.852
You're gonna go with her, Nick,
take a nice swim in the open ocean?

23:44.720 --> 23:45.787
We're not swimming.

23:45.855 --> 23:47.339
We're building a raft.

23:47.406 --> 23:48.340
You're building a raft?

23:48.407 --> 23:49.742
Don't you think

23:49.809 --> 23:51.643
I tried everything
to get off this island?

23:51.710 --> 23:52.528
I built a raft.

23:52.762 --> 23:54.629
Plan was to go
to the next island,

23:54.898 --> 23:57.315
that island you're talking about.

23:57.383 --> 23:58.450
If there was no one there,

23:58.601 --> 24:01.370
we'd resupply and
move to the next one.

24:01.437 --> 24:02.688
Oh, we did it.

24:02.755 --> 24:05.524
Except I didn't
factor in a few things.

24:05.592 --> 24:07.443
This island is a seamount.

24:07.777 --> 24:10.312
That means that
once you pass the reef

24:10.379 --> 24:13.949
it drops down 3,000 feet.

24:15.318 --> 24:16.652
Blue water.

24:16.703 --> 24:18.620
There are two things
you have to watch out for.

24:18.688 --> 24:20.973
After the reef,
there are currents

24:21.040 --> 24:23.392
that are like the jet stream.
You'll get tossed about.

24:23.543 --> 24:26.879
The raft'll get broken apart to
a million different pieces.

24:28.347 --> 24:31.216
And then the sharks.

24:32.518 --> 24:36.588
You've got mako
and oceanic whitetips.

24:36.656 --> 24:38.790
They call them
wolves of the sea.

24:39.075 --> 24:40.826
We were
two miles offshore

24:40.893 --> 24:43.194
on that nice
little raft we built.

24:44.563 --> 24:48.700
And that's when we
ran aground on the reef.

24:52.122 --> 24:54.990
I'm the only one that
made it out.

24:57.227 --> 25:02.264
So don't tell me about trying to
get off this island, Ms. Kope.

25:09.372 --> 25:11.223
The wolves,

25:11.290 --> 25:13.592
they'll come after you
and show no mercy.

25:15.528 --> 25:16.895
God bless you.

25:19.766 --> 25:21.833
Who's coming with us?

25:30.192 --> 25:31.176
I'm coming.

25:35.564 --> 25:37.916
Now, we're gonna need driftwood.

25:37.983 --> 25:41.386
Look on the coastline.
Jugs, plastic bottles,

25:41.454 --> 25:43.405
whatever shit
people throw away,

25:43.473 --> 25:45.140
that's what
we're gonna use.

26:07.346 --> 26:10.648
So what is it you do again?

26:10.716 --> 26:13.051
I'm a hairdresser.

26:26.916 --> 26:28.583
NICK: If anyone
wants to take a break,

26:28.651 --> 26:31.053
someone should probably
get on top of there.

26:31.120 --> 26:33.722
Yeah, Stitch, you're
gonna need a break.

26:33.790 --> 26:35.924
Shut up, man,
Just keep going.

26:47.520 --> 26:49.688
We're almost there.

26:49.856 --> 26:52.140
Nearly there.
Come on. Keep it together.

27:04.637 --> 27:06.071
[ screams ]

27:08.424 --> 27:09.124
Todd?

27:12.011 --> 27:13.612
Oh! There's
a lot of blood!

27:13.680 --> 27:16.298
Oh, my God!
Sharks! Sharks!

28:15.458 --> 28:16.825
Hello?

28:19.695 --> 28:22.364
Hello?
Anyone here?

28:22.432 --> 28:23.731
Hello?

28:23.799 --> 28:26.101
Is there someone there?

28:26.786 --> 28:28.836
Hello? Hello?

28:29.973 --> 28:32.057
<i>Necesito teléfono,</i>
<i>por favor.</i>

28:32.208 --> 28:33.308
<i>Sí. No.</i>

28:35.795 --> 28:37.161
Let me check this door.

28:39.331 --> 28:40.832
Excuse me.

28:42.402 --> 28:44.168
Hello?

28:44.404 --> 28:46.337
Can we use your phone to make a call?
Oh, hi.

28:46.405 --> 28:49.340
<i>¡Vayanse aquí!</i>
<i>Llamada la policia.</i>

28:49.408 --> 28:51.426
<i>Llamada</i>
<i>la policia.</i>

28:51.494 --> 28:53.378
<i>Por favor.</i>

28:54.596 --> 28:56.114
Hey! Hey! Come here.

28:56.181 --> 28:57.449
We need your help!
Wait!

29:01.804 --> 29:03.121
Hello? Hi. Sorry.

29:03.188 --> 29:05.306
Hi. Can you please help us?

29:05.374 --> 29:06.508
Hello? Damn it.

29:06.576 --> 29:09.310
What, they don't like Americans
or something?

29:09.378 --> 29:10.779
Nobody likes Americans.

29:10.847 --> 29:12.781
It's not that.
It's something else.

29:12.849 --> 29:14.282
Oh, shit.

29:22.275 --> 29:24.326
4-3-1.

29:24.394 --> 29:25.193
Huh.

29:25.261 --> 29:27.862
Gave up on you a long time ago.

29:27.930 --> 29:29.631
I thought you were dead.

29:29.698 --> 29:30.949
Yeah.

29:31.017 --> 29:33.852
If you and your pussies get rid
of your stun guns,

29:33.920 --> 29:35.520
then we'll find out
who's dead.

29:36.539 --> 29:37.989
[ chuckles ]

29:40.426 --> 29:42.110
[ coughs ]

29:46.766 --> 29:48.900
You need to learn some manners.

29:49.001 --> 29:51.453
All yours.

29:59.662 --> 30:03.498
Okay, when you're finished,
bag 'em, and tag 'em.

30:05.201 --> 30:07.636
[ groaning ]

30:13.826 --> 30:15.126
[ spits ]

30:23.285 --> 30:25.420
Let's go.

30:26.205 --> 30:28.106
[ winces ]

30:43.122 --> 30:45.256
[ seabirds calling ]

30:53.632 --> 30:55.517
[ groaning ]

31:00.990 --> 31:03.124
No. No.

31:03.192 --> 31:04.209
Damn it.

31:05.711 --> 31:08.312
[ groans ]

31:08.381 --> 31:10.648
Why the hell
didn't they kill us?

31:12.651 --> 31:15.437
I don't know.

31:15.505 --> 31:17.472
Doesn't make sense.

31:21.810 --> 31:23.895
[ coughs ]

31:23.963 --> 31:25.797
Rich.
Yeah?

31:25.931 --> 31:27.081
Girl Sarge brought in

31:27.149 --> 31:28.583
was too far gone.

31:29.535 --> 31:30.819
Shit.

31:30.887 --> 31:32.053
We need a replacement,

31:32.121 --> 31:34.489
preferably one that's
not frickin' dead.

31:34.557 --> 31:37.325
Sarge, the dead girl
you brought us was obviously garbage.

31:37.393 --> 31:39.995
I need you to go back out there
and find somebody else,

31:40.062 --> 31:41.129
preferably in one piece.

31:41.280 --> 31:42.748
We've already
been out there once

31:42.815 --> 31:44.282
to dump those idiots
on the island.

31:44.350 --> 31:46.785
Then go back out again now.

31:46.853 --> 31:48.052
Understood.

31:48.120 --> 31:50.288
The people on that island,
their blood work is perfect.

31:50.355 --> 31:51.740
They've been handpicked.

31:51.807 --> 31:53.792
See, that's what we're
selling here is perfection.

31:53.859 --> 31:56.878
That's a little hard to do
when you beat the shit out of 'em!

31:56.945 --> 31:59.781
I mean it.
Not a scratch!

32:01.166 --> 32:04.402
Okay, guys, let's fall out.

32:04.470 --> 32:07.389
Xander, if Sarge and I
have a falling out,

32:07.456 --> 32:09.407
are you prepared to take over
the operation?

32:10.459 --> 32:12.210
What are you asking me?

32:12.277 --> 32:15.279
Not asking anything yet,
but I think you know what I mean.

32:25.073 --> 32:27.325
What did he want?

32:27.392 --> 32:29.393
He wanted to know what happened
to the girl.

32:29.462 --> 32:32.029
I said it was my fault,
I missed the shot.

32:32.097 --> 32:34.031
He told me not
to mess up again.

32:34.099 --> 32:35.517
What did you say to that?

32:35.585 --> 32:37.118
Well, I told him

32:37.186 --> 32:39.354
maybe if he thinks he could do
a better job,

32:39.422 --> 32:40.922
he should come along with us

32:40.990 --> 32:42.290
and take one out himself.

32:59.808 --> 33:03.611
You two go on. Not you.

33:06.282 --> 33:08.817
So you wanna take over, eh?

33:08.884 --> 33:10.151
No.

33:10.219 --> 33:11.937
Did he ask you to kill me?

33:12.004 --> 33:13.205
No.

33:13.272 --> 33:15.623
I don't believe you.

33:17.160 --> 33:18.559
Let's go.

33:25.151 --> 33:26.484
[ grunts ]

33:26.552 --> 33:28.269
There's only room
for one leader here.

33:47.289 --> 33:49.690
[ brush rustling ]

34:38.239 --> 34:39.674
[ blade slashes ]

34:47.833 --> 34:49.766
[ steady whine ]

34:53.737 --> 34:55.672
[ whimpering ]

35:05.333 --> 35:06.550
What's that?

35:06.618 --> 35:08.419
Think it's an ear.

35:08.437 --> 35:09.854
Yeah, I can see that.

35:09.921 --> 35:11.806
Oh, my God.

35:11.874 --> 35:13.407
[ sobs ]

35:13.475 --> 35:15.843
Oh, God.

35:15.911 --> 35:17.912
Oh, shit. Oh, my God.
She's going into shock.

35:17.980 --> 35:19.246
Okay, we gotta
get back to camp.

35:19.314 --> 35:20.648
Oh, my God.
Come on.

35:21.700 --> 35:24.535
If you take things
into your own hands again,

35:24.603 --> 35:26.621
that will be
your ear on that machete,

35:26.689 --> 35:29.040
and it won't be no accident.
You understand?

35:31.944 --> 35:33.010
What happened?

35:33.078 --> 35:34.579
They cut her ear off!

35:34.647 --> 35:35.380
What do we do?

35:35.447 --> 35:36.781
Put her here.
Put her here!

35:36.848 --> 35:38.416
Jean, get some firewood!

35:40.135 --> 35:41.252
I've got to cauterize this.

35:41.404 --> 35:43.037
Make a fire quick.
Hey!

35:43.105 --> 35:44.188
Where's Todd?

35:44.256 --> 35:45.423
He didn't make it.

35:46.041 --> 35:47.359
You happy now, Billie?

35:47.426 --> 35:49.344
They trusted you.

35:49.411 --> 35:51.595
All right,
we gotta keep her warm.

35:51.663 --> 35:52.430
Okay.

36:07.146 --> 36:09.664
[ brush rustles ]

36:11.817 --> 36:13.401
[ wings flap ]

37:09.024 --> 37:10.524
[ frogs croaking ]

37:10.726 --> 37:13.677
Okay, tonight we're gonna swim
back to the island.

37:13.745 --> 37:14.929
Why?

37:15.497 --> 37:16.714
I mean,
there must be

37:16.782 --> 37:18.549
some method to their
madness. I mean,

37:18.617 --> 37:20.385
why would they just bring us
back here

37:20.452 --> 37:21.252
to hunt us down again?

37:21.320 --> 37:24.622
A sociological experiment?

37:24.689 --> 37:28.475
Some sick human hunting game
for rich people?

37:29.812 --> 37:30.878
I don't know.

37:44.393 --> 37:49.847
I have a sister...

37:49.914 --> 37:51.382
Rina.

37:54.119 --> 37:56.137
We've always been different.

37:56.205 --> 37:57.671
She took after our mother,

37:57.739 --> 38:01.609
liked girlie things, shopping.

38:01.676 --> 38:04.495
Not me.

38:04.563 --> 38:05.830
I was Daddy's girl.

38:05.897 --> 38:07.481
Hold that jab.
He was a judo champion

38:07.549 --> 38:09.233
back in the Soviet Union

38:09.301 --> 38:11.886
and an officer in the Army.

38:11.954 --> 38:13.738
Jab, right cross.
Follow with that right cross.

38:13.806 --> 38:16.424
He started training me
as early as I can remember.

38:16.491 --> 38:18.543
That's it. Go deep.
That's it.

38:18.610 --> 38:20.027
Okay, don't be afraid.

38:20.095 --> 38:21.078
That's okay.

38:21.230 --> 38:22.296
Don't be afraid.

38:22.364 --> 38:23.647
That's it.

38:23.715 --> 38:25.783
Don't be afraid.
That's it.

38:25.851 --> 38:27.918
That's it.

38:29.071 --> 38:30.355
I got you.

38:30.422 --> 38:32.056
You're okay.

38:33.175 --> 38:34.859
That's it.

38:34.926 --> 38:36.327
[ coughing ]

38:36.395 --> 38:38.279
Good, good, good.

38:38.347 --> 38:39.364
You were choking me.

38:39.431 --> 38:41.683
Yes, but I need you
not to be afraid of it.

38:41.750 --> 38:44.368
How does your mom
feel about all that?

38:44.436 --> 38:45.987
She didn't feel anything.

38:48.307 --> 38:50.341
She was already dead.

38:51.827 --> 38:52.726
I'm sorry.

38:54.580 --> 38:56.447
What happened to her?

38:56.514 --> 38:58.983
It was a robbery.

38:59.051 --> 39:00.718
It went bad.

39:02.738 --> 39:05.372
That's why it was
so important for our father

39:05.440 --> 39:07.408
that his daughters learn
how to fight.

39:07.610 --> 39:10.978
Faster! Faster! Faster!

39:11.046 --> 39:12.980
That's what I'm looking for.

39:13.933 --> 39:17.118
Ah, that's it.
That's it.

39:17.186 --> 39:18.953
Relax.

39:19.021 --> 39:21.122
That's it.

39:21.190 --> 39:23.006
Breathe.

39:23.074 --> 39:24.408
Okay.

39:24.476 --> 39:25.543
That's it.
Hold it. Hold it.

39:25.694 --> 39:26.861
Now push yourself up.

39:26.928 --> 39:27.862
Lift yourself.

39:27.930 --> 39:29.247
No thinking.
No mind.

39:29.314 --> 39:30.548
No thinking!
Lift. Lift.

39:30.615 --> 39:32.583
Lift. Lift. Do it.

39:32.651 --> 39:34.402
That's it.
Again. Down.

39:34.469 --> 39:36.337
That's it.
Concentrate. You can do this!

39:36.404 --> 39:38.289
Come on. Work.
Work. Hold it.

39:38.624 --> 39:39.323
Hold it there.

39:39.391 --> 39:41.225
Hold it there.
Hold it there.

39:41.293 --> 39:43.160
Push! Push it up.
Push it up!

39:43.228 --> 39:44.395
[ groaning ]
Push.

39:44.462 --> 39:45.396
That's it.

39:45.463 --> 39:47.181
One more time, last time.

39:47.249 --> 39:48.616
Come on.
You can do this.

39:48.683 --> 39:51.669
Go down.
Go down slowly.

39:51.737 --> 39:52.736
That's it.
Breathe.

39:52.804 --> 39:54.272
If you can't carry your body weight,

39:54.339 --> 39:55.756
you can't do advanced technique.

39:55.824 --> 39:57.408
Work it. That's it.
There you go.

39:57.476 --> 40:00.327
Okay, push from internal. Go.

40:00.395 --> 40:02.263
Don't look down.
Don't look down.

40:02.330 --> 40:04.865
Push! Push! Push!

40:04.933 --> 40:05.516
[ groans ]
Good job.

40:05.583 --> 40:07.602
Breathe! Breathe!
Push up,

40:07.669 --> 40:09.486
all the way up.
Good job.

40:09.554 --> 40:10.839
[ groans ]

40:10.906 --> 40:12.390
Jab, right cross.
Here.

40:12.457 --> 40:14.158
Okay,
now this time--

40:14.260 --> 40:16.678
Come on! Grab my weight!
Put your chin into my shoulder!

40:16.745 --> 40:17.945
There you go.
Push it down.

40:18.013 --> 40:19.513
Bring my wrist down.
That's it.

40:19.581 --> 40:21.131
Now pull out.
Put it up. Hold it.

40:21.199 --> 40:23.134
Hold it there.
Very good.

40:23.202 --> 40:24.669
Nice job.

40:24.737 --> 40:27.605
Well, Rina rebelled
after our mother was killed.

40:27.673 --> 40:30.174
She moved to New York

40:30.241 --> 40:32.577
and got deep into heroin.

40:32.644 --> 40:35.496
Dad cut her off,
but she just blamed him

40:35.563 --> 40:37.732
for not being there for our mother.

40:37.799 --> 40:40.051
I got so angry with her.

40:40.118 --> 40:43.988
I told her I wished
she would just disappear,

40:44.056 --> 40:46.057
and she did.

40:46.158 --> 40:48.709
She was arrested in Juarez
six years ago

40:48.777 --> 40:51.095
for possession
of heroin and cocaine.

40:51.163 --> 40:55.116
I guess you could say
she has a bit of a problem.

40:56.718 --> 40:59.020
She has a good heart, though.

40:59.738 --> 41:00.955
And if this whole thing

41:01.022 --> 41:03.274
is not connected, then I've got

41:03.341 --> 41:05.309
the worst luck in the world.

41:07.663 --> 41:09.697
Well, you met me.

41:09.765 --> 41:11.566
That's kind of lucky.

41:11.633 --> 41:12.816
Heh.

41:14.219 --> 41:15.320
[ chuckles ]

41:23.094 --> 41:24.478
Hey...

41:36.308 --> 41:37.892
Ahem!

41:37.960 --> 41:39.560
Guys, come on.

41:39.911 --> 41:41.545
We need to get to shelter
before it gets dark.

41:41.613 --> 41:43.614
Come on. Let's go.
Let's go.

41:49.254 --> 41:51.038
Come on.

41:51.106 --> 41:54.208
Quentin, what's the nature
of this call?

41:54.276 --> 41:55.659
Is it an emergency?
You tell me.

41:55.727 --> 41:57.661
I got one of the kids
with a missing ear.

41:57.729 --> 42:00.064
Who was it?
Chloe.

42:00.065 --> 42:02.483
Well, they're bringing
somebody else in, right?

42:02.551 --> 42:03.267
Yeah. They got the--

42:03.334 --> 42:04.718
They got another match,
all right?

42:04.786 --> 42:05.987
Listen, we need to go over
a few things, Rich.

42:06.054 --> 42:07.104
Look, it'll have to wait, okay?

42:07.172 --> 42:08.756
We've got a little bit
of a full plate

42:08.774 --> 42:09.891
over here
with this Mao thing.

42:09.958 --> 42:10.841
No, it's not gonna wait.

42:10.909 --> 42:12.326
I'm done.
You got it?

42:12.394 --> 42:13.143
I want out of here.

42:13.211 --> 42:14.261
What are you talking about?

42:14.329 --> 42:15.346
I'm not gonna keep up

42:15.497 --> 42:16.464
the charade anymore.
I'm finished.

42:16.531 --> 42:17.531
I'm tired of wiping my ass

42:17.599 --> 42:18.632
with banana leaves.
You got it?

42:18.700 --> 42:20.534
It was supposed to last a month,

42:20.602 --> 42:21.352
not a permanent thing!

42:21.420 --> 42:22.670
I want out!
I'm done!

42:22.737 --> 42:24.404
Quentin, what is this?

42:24.472 --> 42:25.740
You trying to renegotiate?

42:25.807 --> 42:27.691
Renegotiate?
Are you crazy?

42:27.759 --> 42:28.909
No, I want off the island.

42:28.977 --> 42:30.211
It's as simple as that.

42:30.278 --> 42:32.863
And you'll get off
the island as promised,

42:32.931 --> 42:35.416
and you'll be rich
as promised, all right?

42:35.484 --> 42:37.935
Just give me
a little bit more time.

42:39.021 --> 42:39.753
How much?

42:39.821 --> 42:41.438
Until this business
with Mao

42:41.506 --> 42:42.723
is taken care of.

42:42.791 --> 42:44.274
[ sighs ]
No, you're better off

42:44.342 --> 42:45.776
with me over there with you.

42:45.844 --> 42:47.695
That can't happen right now.

42:47.763 --> 42:48.946
You get me off this island,

42:49.014 --> 42:51.432
either your way or I'll do it
my way,

42:51.500 --> 42:52.766
and you know I can.

43:15.857 --> 43:18.075
They don't know about
this place.

43:18.143 --> 43:20.244
It's got
fresh running water.

43:20.311 --> 43:23.331
As long as you don't mind
the bats, it's all good.

43:50.092 --> 43:53.327
Those markings
on the wall, Stitch...

43:53.395 --> 43:55.479
are they for the days
you've been here?

43:55.547 --> 43:56.964
'Cause there's more than 44.

43:57.032 --> 43:58.666
Uh-uh.
That's how many people

43:58.734 --> 44:01.251
have since showed up
since I been here.

44:02.187 --> 44:05.155
So many of them.

44:06.475 --> 44:08.776
Any of them could be her.

44:14.966 --> 44:18.069
Hey, guys, I made up a couple
of hammocks over there.

44:18.136 --> 44:20.354
It's better than sleeping
on the rocks, that's for sure.

44:20.422 --> 44:22.006
Oh, thank you.

44:46.981 --> 44:49.116
[ thunder crashing ]

44:58.560 --> 44:59.827
That's Mao?

44:59.894 --> 45:02.446
I've only ever spoken
to the assistant.

45:02.513 --> 45:04.332
[ thunder crashes ]

45:04.399 --> 45:07.401
Ms. Mao, it is so nice
to finally meet you in person.

45:07.469 --> 45:08.602
I'm Rich Napier.

45:08.870 --> 45:12.206
I do hope your journey
was--was pleasant.

45:12.273 --> 45:13.424
It's Mao.

45:13.492 --> 45:15.643
Of course.

45:15.711 --> 45:18.796
And this
must be Violet. Hi.

45:19.181 --> 45:22.132
Mao, Violet is
in the best of hands.

45:22.200 --> 45:23.968
Our fine doctor,
Dr. Walsh,

45:24.135 --> 45:26.254
is a hepatobiliary specialist.
In fact,

45:26.321 --> 45:27.504
he's pioneered several
breakthroughs in the field.

45:27.572 --> 45:30.190
He is without a doubt the
best surgeon money can buy.

45:31.927 --> 45:33.410
Nice to meet you.

45:35.663 --> 45:38.148
You have kids?

45:39.568 --> 45:40.801
Somewhere, daughter.

45:40.868 --> 45:42.753
What's her name?

45:42.821 --> 45:44.705
Ruby. Why?

45:45.007 --> 45:47.091
Pretty name.

45:49.545 --> 45:51.045
Hey, sweetie.

45:51.113 --> 45:52.947
I'm gonna make you
feel better.

45:53.014 --> 45:56.834
I promise, okay?

45:58.036 --> 45:59.236
Now you and Violet

45:59.471 --> 46:00.788
will want for nothing
while you're here.

46:00.856 --> 46:02.339
We have a lovely suite
for you upstairs,

46:02.407 --> 46:05.375
and we have places set for
your men in the outer compound.

46:05.443 --> 46:06.661
They stay with me.

46:06.728 --> 46:08.128
Of course.

46:10.948 --> 46:15.603
Baby, last time, okay?

46:15.670 --> 46:17.003
Promise.

46:17.071 --> 46:19.240
You heard that man promise.

46:19.307 --> 46:22.243
And that one looks like
your ferret.

46:22.310 --> 46:23.844
[ laughs ]

46:23.912 --> 46:25.630
Ah, there's my smile.

46:26.430 --> 46:29.667
It's like the sunshine!

46:29.734 --> 46:32.703
Swear it gets hotter
when you smile.

46:32.771 --> 46:35.689
You go spread that sunshine around
this place, okay?

46:35.757 --> 46:37.824
I'll come find you
in a little bit.

46:37.892 --> 46:38.825
[ pats ]

46:38.893 --> 46:40.026
I love you.

46:40.094 --> 46:42.229
[ thunder crashing ]

46:46.051 --> 46:47.701
I'll look forward to seeing
the facilities.

46:47.769 --> 46:49.320
Please, follow me.

46:49.388 --> 46:50.654
Yeah.

46:50.722 --> 46:53.290
Proper medical data encryption
and Latin America

46:53.357 --> 46:54.792
don't necessarily go hand in hand.

46:54.859 --> 46:55.910
When someone comes in

46:55.977 --> 46:57.744
for a blood test or dental work,

46:57.812 --> 46:59.246
it all goes into a database.

46:59.314 --> 47:00.998
My Estonian boys have the code

47:01.232 --> 47:02.366
to sift through that data.

47:02.433 --> 47:04.935
If we find somebody
with good statistics,

47:05.003 --> 47:07.638
like a certain
blood-type, right,

47:07.706 --> 47:09.940
no diseases, perfect health,

47:10.007 --> 47:11.558
we target and track them.

47:11.626 --> 47:12.226
Track 'em?

47:12.294 --> 47:13.844
Yeah, it's easy
these days.

47:13.912 --> 47:15.913
I mean,
you have cellphones.

47:15.980 --> 47:16.897
You have
credit card statements,

47:16.965 --> 47:18.982
uh, social networking,
laptops.

47:19.050 --> 47:21.385
As soon as we find them,
my boys bag 'em.

47:21.453 --> 47:23.320
They bring them here
to our private island,

47:23.388 --> 47:25.222
and after a few weeks of
fruits, vegetables,

47:25.289 --> 47:27.941
and pure island drinking water,
their bodies are clean.

47:28.009 --> 47:30.493
Then we wait for clients
like yourself to call us,

47:30.561 --> 47:32.996
and we have our whole stable
of donors just waiting.

47:33.064 --> 47:37.284
When the client shows up, within hours,
we can harvest the donor.

47:37.352 --> 47:38.368
Hmm.

47:39.788 --> 47:41.371
I'd like to see Violet's donor.

47:41.439 --> 47:45.025
Eh, we don't generally do that.

47:45.092 --> 47:47.378
It's not a request.
No, I understand,

47:47.445 --> 47:49.029
but we've had
a couple of clients

47:49.097 --> 47:50.598
change their mind
after seeing the donor.

47:50.666 --> 47:51.782
I hate to use this word,

47:51.850 --> 47:54.235
but it humanizes them.

47:54.302 --> 47:56.203
I promise you, Mao,
Violet is in good hands.

47:56.271 --> 47:59.440
We will take
excellent care of her.

48:30.405 --> 48:33.073
I, uh--
I wouldn't swim in there.

48:33.141 --> 48:37.327
There's a lot
of snakes in there.

48:37.395 --> 48:39.880
The leeches, too,
they're--

48:39.947 --> 48:41.565
Breakfast is ready.

48:43.334 --> 48:45.185
I'll just--
I'll wait over here.

48:48.073 --> 48:49.623
[ men yelling ]

48:49.725 --> 48:52.259
Whoa! Whoa!
Whoa! Whoa! What's going on?

48:52.611 --> 48:54.394
There's a problem with
the specimen.

48:54.462 --> 48:55.162
What?

48:56.681 --> 48:58.615
Donor's unacceptable.

48:59.984 --> 49:01.585
She has no chi.

49:01.652 --> 49:04.204
I'm sorry, but no chi

49:04.272 --> 49:05.806
is not a viable medical condition.

49:05.874 --> 49:07.808
With all due respect,
Mao,

49:07.876 --> 49:09.209
this donor was handpicked

49:09.444 --> 49:11.561
and primed as a perfect match
for your daughter.

49:11.663 --> 49:13.680
I mean, we've gone
through great lengths

49:13.748 --> 49:16.016
to make sure that she's the
perfect specimen for this procedure.

49:16.251 --> 49:18.085
Look into that woman's eyes.

49:18.420 --> 49:22.556
Do you see
the thousand-mile stare?

49:23.441 --> 49:25.759
Hmm?

49:25.827 --> 49:27.428
She's broken.

49:28.229 --> 49:30.781
She has accepted her demise.

49:30.848 --> 49:32.833
She has no fight!

49:32.901 --> 49:36.970
Right now, her body is being
flooded with fear hormones,

49:37.038 --> 49:38.923
adrenaline, and bile.

49:38.990 --> 49:41.575
It's poisoning
her entire system!

49:41.643 --> 49:43.577
She is weak!

49:47.231 --> 49:49.049
I need someone strong.

49:49.116 --> 49:50.901
Very well.

49:50.969 --> 49:53.720
Dr. Walsh,
Mao is paying premium.

49:53.788 --> 49:55.322
She gets what she asks for.

49:55.389 --> 49:56.323
Thank you.

49:56.491 --> 49:59.326
If this girl
doesn't have enough chi,

49:59.394 --> 50:00.628
she doesn't have
enough chi.

50:00.695 --> 50:02.263
We'll find her
a suitable replacement.

50:02.330 --> 50:03.664
But we need to operate now.

50:03.732 --> 50:06.817
Every hour we waste risks
that little girl's life.

50:11.873 --> 50:14.408
I want one of those.

50:17.261 --> 50:19.146
I want her.

50:20.314 --> 50:24.234
Sure. Uh, that can be arranged.

50:25.420 --> 50:28.538
Dr. Walsh, change of plans.

50:28.606 --> 50:30.774
MJ?

50:30.842 --> 50:32.726
Thank you, gentlemen.

50:34.362 --> 50:36.129
Out.

50:38.400 --> 50:41.251
Won't let you down.

50:48.342 --> 50:51.545
Walsh, prep the girl
from yesterday.

50:51.612 --> 50:54.381
Screw Mao. She's not
gonna know the difference.

50:57.602 --> 51:00.787
What about that girl
on the island?

51:01.705 --> 51:03.140
I-I'll have them kill her.

51:03.207 --> 51:05.392
She wasn't brought here
for her blood work anyway.

51:05.460 --> 51:07.361
She was asking around
about me,

51:07.428 --> 51:09.479
specifically me.

51:09.547 --> 51:11.732
I just had her put here
so I could find out

51:11.799 --> 51:13.534
who she's working with
and what she knows.

51:13.601 --> 51:15.435
I thought it would be
a good idea

51:15.503 --> 51:16.871
to put her with
a sympathetic ear,

51:16.938 --> 51:19.073
but Quentin has apparently
dropped the ball on that.

51:19.140 --> 51:21.075
I'm not sure
what to do with her.

51:23.678 --> 51:27.330
I think you should do what
you feel's right.

51:29.384 --> 51:31.235
That's my girl.

51:36.424 --> 51:38.309
[ monitor beeping ]

52:13.277 --> 52:14.428
Hey.

52:24.338 --> 52:26.673
[ groaning ]

52:29.760 --> 52:31.395
[ blade slices ]

52:34.632 --> 52:38.351
All right.
We'll have to be quick about this.

52:39.153 --> 52:41.071
NICK:
Too heavy, Stitch.

52:41.139 --> 52:41.822
BILLIE:
Am I hurting you?

52:41.890 --> 52:43.490
No. Am I hurting you?
No.

52:43.558 --> 52:45.626
What the hell
is going on here?

52:45.693 --> 52:49.246
Put her down!
Put her down now!

52:54.368 --> 52:55.802
Is that you, Nick?

52:58.822 --> 53:01.892
[ laughing ]

53:04.812 --> 53:06.563
You're with them!

53:06.630 --> 53:07.480
No, but you are.

53:07.682 --> 53:09.966
All along,
you were with them!

53:10.034 --> 53:11.201
Oh, come on. Stop it!

53:11.269 --> 53:12.218
We see right through you.

53:12.570 --> 53:15.155
Back up!
Just stay away!

53:15.222 --> 53:16.139
Back up!

53:19.076 --> 53:20.510
You see nothing.

53:30.705 --> 53:34.091
It's gonna be tough
going up against them.

53:37.044 --> 53:38.178
Good luck.

53:38.246 --> 53:39.913
[ laughs ]

53:39.981 --> 53:42.315
I'm outta here.

53:42.383 --> 53:44.734
<i>Sayonara!</i>

53:44.802 --> 53:45.635
[ laughs ]

54:40.090 --> 54:41.108
[ groans ]

54:44.279 --> 54:47.581
Okay, guys, this is
do or die for us.

54:47.648 --> 54:49.199
We have to take that boat,

54:49.266 --> 54:50.567
no matter who we meet,

54:50.635 --> 54:52.635
no matter what
we encounter, okay?

54:52.703 --> 54:54.304
We will.

54:54.372 --> 54:56.489
Okay, let's go.

55:40.267 --> 55:41.001
Shh.

55:55.950 --> 55:57.267
Ah-ah-ah-ah.

55:57.335 --> 55:58.502
Don't move.

56:06.694 --> 56:08.762
BILLIE:
You guys can have the boat.

56:08.830 --> 56:11.164
Go wherever you want.
You're free now.

56:12.300 --> 56:14.434
But first,
you're dropping me off.

56:14.502 --> 56:15.702
NICK:
Are you crazy?

56:15.770 --> 56:16.803
I'm not going anywhere

56:16.954 --> 56:19.088
without finding out
what's going on here.

56:19.156 --> 56:22.158
So there's no way we
could change your mind?

56:23.244 --> 56:25.495
Not on this.

56:25.563 --> 56:26.546
Seriously?

56:26.614 --> 56:29.833
You have that low
of an opinion of me?

56:31.469 --> 56:33.687
What about you, Stitch?

56:33.754 --> 56:35.856
What am I supposed
to say, eh?

56:36.023 --> 56:37.490
We made it this far,
didn't we?

56:37.558 --> 56:39.226
[ laughs ]

56:39.294 --> 56:40.960
Be rude not to, really.

56:41.028 --> 56:42.079
[ laughs ]

56:42.230 --> 56:43.497
Thank you.

56:49.654 --> 56:52.855
What's
our operational status?

56:52.874 --> 56:54.625
Surgery on Song Mao
is under way now.

56:54.692 --> 56:57.210
And the, uh, mission
to the island?

56:57.277 --> 56:59.679
No report yet.

57:00.531 --> 57:03.083
I'll be in me quarters
if you need me.

57:07.388 --> 57:09.689
[ overlapping chatter
in Spanish ]

57:19.416 --> 57:22.119
Well, hello there,
little lady.

57:22.186 --> 57:23.219
[ gasps ]

57:27.908 --> 57:31.111
You want a job working on
a private island?

57:57.638 --> 57:59.222
We've got complications.

58:06.263 --> 58:08.098
What?

58:10.334 --> 58:13.119
She's had the Kasha procedure,
hasn't she?

58:15.706 --> 58:18.525
Well, it's resulted in
biliary atresia.

58:18.593 --> 58:20.393
RICH:
Speak English.

58:20.461 --> 58:21.894
Her bile duct
isn't functioning.

58:21.962 --> 58:24.297
I don't know if
the new liver'll help.

58:27.168 --> 58:29.235
And I don't care
what you have to do, Walsh.

58:29.303 --> 58:31.671
You get back in there right now,
and you save her.

58:31.739 --> 58:33.006
Yeah, I will,

58:33.074 --> 58:34.557
but we've gotta be prepared to--

58:34.625 --> 58:35.842
Walsh, fix it!

58:35.910 --> 58:38.178
You want to
come up here and do it?!

58:43.367 --> 58:45.201
[ gasps ]

58:45.269 --> 58:47.637
I came...

59:03.554 --> 59:06.906
Doesn't look like the dock's
guarded, you know.

59:08.125 --> 59:10.143
Yeah, well, there might be
some people around the house.

59:12.229 --> 59:14.263
What are we waiting for?

59:18.569 --> 59:21.137
Hey, guys, wait!
Stop! Stop.

59:22.890 --> 59:26.410
Look, uh,

59:26.477 --> 59:28.645
I've got
an admission to make.

59:31.014 --> 59:32.932
I'm not in the S.A.S.

59:34.885 --> 59:36.803
I mean,
I went for special ops.

59:36.871 --> 59:40.757
Just that, well, I got washed out
of their training program.

59:41.893 --> 59:43.526
I mean, I'm military.

59:43.594 --> 59:46.162
Heh. Well,
did the basic training.

59:46.230 --> 59:50.783
It's just that I'm not
like those guys out there.

59:51.418 --> 59:54.353
They're trained killers.

59:55.740 --> 59:57.907
You weren't taken into a
battlefield hospital?

59:59.627 --> 01:00:01.027
No.

01:00:01.229 --> 01:00:03.012
Oh, I mean,
I was hospitalized,

01:00:03.080 --> 01:00:05.599
but not
from the front line.

01:00:06.634 --> 01:00:08.101
I got food poisoning.

01:00:09.536 --> 01:00:11.121
I work
in the mess hall.

01:00:12.890 --> 01:00:14.758
What about Afghanistan,
the two times wounded?

01:00:14.825 --> 01:00:16.225
Didn't you say that?

01:00:17.662 --> 01:00:20.129
But you've been
in combat before, right?

01:00:21.281 --> 01:00:23.700
Before today, no.

01:00:23.767 --> 01:00:25.585
Heh. Great.

01:00:25.653 --> 01:00:27.170
I knew something was up

01:00:27.238 --> 01:00:29.823
when you said how long you
were on the island.

01:00:29.890 --> 01:00:33.026
A Special Ops soldier
on an island for 44 days?

01:00:33.094 --> 01:00:35.728
Two months?
Doing what? Nothing?

01:00:37.198 --> 01:00:38.698
Sorry.

01:00:39.666 --> 01:00:41.117
[ sighs ]
Look, Stitch,

01:00:41.185 --> 01:00:44.020
you can stay here with the boat
if you want to, okay?

01:00:44.088 --> 01:00:46.222
Nick, you're coming
with me, right?

01:00:48.258 --> 01:00:53.079
We'll come back for you, okay?

01:00:54.248 --> 01:00:55.398
No, no, no.

01:00:55.466 --> 01:00:57.400
Wait, wait, wait.
Just wait.

01:00:57.468 --> 01:00:58.050
[ sighs ]

01:00:58.118 --> 01:01:00.219
Look, if it
wasn't for you guys,

01:01:00.404 --> 01:01:03.606
we'd still be stuck
on that island, right?

01:01:05.159 --> 01:01:07.927
I owe you guys my life.

01:01:08.963 --> 01:01:11.381
I'm coming, all right?
I'm coming.

01:01:53.340 --> 01:01:55.792
[ exhales ]

01:01:55.860 --> 01:01:56.926
On the count of three.

01:01:56.994 --> 01:01:58.845
Okay.
Okay.

01:01:58.912 --> 01:02:01.263
1, 2, 3.

01:02:03.734 --> 01:02:05.251
Just give me a minute.

01:02:08.222 --> 01:02:09.405
[ grunts ]

01:02:15.947 --> 01:02:17.296
[ neck cracks ]

01:02:36.750 --> 01:02:38.835
[ flies buzzing ]

01:02:47.344 --> 01:02:48.395
Clear.

01:02:51.432 --> 01:02:52.915
[ coughs ]

01:03:07.531 --> 01:03:09.565
[ gasping ]

01:03:29.503 --> 01:03:31.587
Oh, my God.

01:03:42.015 --> 01:03:44.166
It's Jean.

01:03:48.505 --> 01:03:50.439
Holy shit.

01:03:53.143 --> 01:03:56.045
They're organ thieves.

01:03:56.113 --> 01:03:58.915
They're harvesting us

01:03:58.983 --> 01:04:01.250
for this, our organs.

01:04:05.773 --> 01:04:07.524
An organ farm.

01:04:31.182 --> 01:04:33.165
Where's Sarge?

01:04:33.250 --> 01:04:35.585
ANNOUNCER:
20,000 Polish fans

01:04:35.653 --> 01:04:37.119
are packed into Wembley.

01:04:37.187 --> 01:04:39.239
It's an electric atmosphere.

01:04:39.306 --> 01:04:41.524
[ radio continues indistinctly ]

01:04:46.863 --> 01:04:48.514
Well back.

01:04:48.582 --> 01:04:49.732
He's falling in.

01:04:49.800 --> 01:04:51.317
[ continues indistinctly ]

01:04:52.069 --> 01:04:53.853
That was an excellent move

01:04:53.921 --> 01:04:55.855
by Wayne to get it down.

01:04:55.923 --> 01:04:57.289
It takes you there.

01:04:57.357 --> 01:04:59.675
There's a chance
to break out here.

01:04:59.827 --> 01:05:00.960
Taking it across here.

01:05:01.028 --> 01:05:02.712
Hits the bar! No!

01:05:02.779 --> 01:05:04.380
Ah, into the side netting.

01:05:05.432 --> 01:05:07.233
Reporting for England there.

01:05:07.301 --> 01:05:10.253
Look at the space.
In the clear.

01:05:10.320 --> 01:05:13.873
Once again, Poland looking
to counterattack here.

01:05:13.940 --> 01:05:15.841
Oh, it's been left beautifully.

01:05:15.909 --> 01:05:17.927
Lewandowski into the area,

01:05:17.995 --> 01:05:20.496
and he's pulled his shot wide.

01:05:20.564 --> 01:05:22.832
He can barely believe it.

01:05:22.900 --> 01:05:26.268
[ continues indistinctly ]

01:05:26.336 --> 01:05:28.070
England stretched at the back.

01:05:28.139 --> 01:05:30.706
Townsend on the charge.

01:05:30.774 --> 01:05:32.425
Smalling is offside here.

01:05:32.493 --> 01:05:33.876
Here's the ball back.
Way to go.

01:05:33.944 --> 01:05:35.444
And it's Townsend.

01:05:35.512 --> 01:05:36.345
Hits the bar!

01:05:36.413 --> 01:05:38.197
[ continues indistinctly ]

01:05:38.265 --> 01:05:40.299
Ball straight to the keeper.

01:05:40.367 --> 01:05:43.986
Ah, England highly
under pressure.

01:05:44.054 --> 01:05:46.222
And with Townsend
rattling the crossbar.

01:05:46.290 --> 01:05:48.858
Sturridge on the follow.

01:05:48.926 --> 01:05:50.893
[ continues indistinctly ]

01:05:52.880 --> 01:05:54.580
Oh, Sturridge!

01:05:54.648 --> 01:05:55.732
It goes wide!

01:05:55.799 --> 01:05:56.933
They fall back.

01:05:57.001 --> 01:05:59.035
What an unbelievable miss.

01:06:00.203 --> 01:06:02.021
Sturridge right to left,

01:06:02.088 --> 01:06:04.573
goes right instead,

01:06:04.641 --> 01:06:06.325
drives down the middle.

01:06:06.393 --> 01:06:07.760
Ball in under pressure here.

01:06:07.828 --> 01:06:09.912
Ah, it's left of beam.

01:06:09.980 --> 01:06:11.597
It's Wayne Rooney!

01:06:11.665 --> 01:06:13.366
England takes the lead!

01:06:13.433 --> 01:06:16.686
And Wembley breathes
a sigh of relief.

01:06:16.687 --> 01:06:19.421
Beautiful ball in for Wayne.

01:06:21.408 --> 01:06:23.142
[ continues indistinctly ]

01:06:23.210 --> 01:06:24.593
[ door clicks ]

01:06:35.638 --> 01:06:37.557
[ gasps ]

01:06:37.625 --> 01:06:39.291
[ sobs ]

01:06:43.813 --> 01:06:46.032
[ footsteps clattering ]

01:06:53.757 --> 01:06:54.924
[ door opens ]

01:06:54.992 --> 01:06:57.177
[ monitor whining ]

01:07:01.899 --> 01:07:04.283
[ crying ]

01:07:08.789 --> 01:07:11.574
Shh.

01:07:55.703 --> 01:07:57.219
Whoa! Whoa!

01:07:57.321 --> 01:07:59.339
Don't shoot!
Don't shoot!

01:07:59.406 --> 01:08:00.305
We can work this out!

01:08:00.591 --> 01:08:03.026
Just hold on!
Wait! One moment!

01:08:03.093 --> 01:08:05.011
[ Rich yelling ]

01:08:05.079 --> 01:08:05.811
[ gunshot ]

01:08:05.879 --> 01:08:07.597
Stop! No! Stop!

01:08:17.124 --> 01:08:19.392
RICH:
Wait, okay? Hold on!

01:08:19.459 --> 01:08:21.560
We can settle this now.

01:08:21.627 --> 01:08:22.795
Hold on!

01:08:32.622 --> 01:08:33.790
Stop.

01:08:35.893 --> 01:08:37.658
[ gasps ]

01:08:51.725 --> 01:08:55.327
Mao, it is this woman's fault
right here.

01:08:55.395 --> 01:08:57.596
Our first two donors
died because of her.

01:08:57.665 --> 01:09:00.533
Your daughter would still be alive
right now if it weren't for her!

01:09:00.600 --> 01:09:04.203
Lies!
You stole my sister.

01:09:04.270 --> 01:09:06.104
You are the cause of this.

01:09:06.171 --> 01:09:09.175
You're pathetic.
Hold on.

